    <h3>Obverse</h3>
    
        <p>Female head with laurel wreath facing left, dividing the country name on both sides. Names of the designer and engraver below.</p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Script:</strong>
        Latin    </p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Lettering:</strong>
        <br />        <span id="obverse_lettering" class="lettering">REPVBBLICA ITALIANA<br />
ROMAGNOLI<br />
GIAMPAOLI-INC.</span>
    </p>
            
        
        <p>
        <strong>Translation:</strong>
                ITALIAN REPUBLIC    </p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Engraver:</strong>
        <a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/artist.php?id=2312">Pietro Giampaoli</a>    </p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Designer:</strong>
        <a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/artist.php?id=371">Giuseppe Romagnoli</a>    </p>
    
    <h3>Reverse</h3>
    
        <p>Goddess Minerva facing left reaching an olive tree with her raised right hand while in the left holds a long spear. Value at left of olive trunk; mintmark at right of the Goddess. Date below, in exergue.</p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Script:</strong>
        Latin    </p>
        
        <p>
        <strong>Lettering:</strong>
        <br />        <span id="reverse_lettering" class="lettering">L.100 R<br />
1967</span>
    </p>
            
        
        
        <p>
        <strong>Engraver:</strong>
        <a href="https://en.numista.com/catalogue/artist.php?id=371">Giuseppe Romagnoli</a>    </p>
        
    
    <h3>Edge</h3>
    
        <p>Reeded</p>
        
        
        
        
    
